-- Barclays Africa H1 earnings up 10 pct
-- By Helen Nyambura-Mwaura
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 01:28AM EDT
-- None



JOHANNESBURG, July 30 (Reuters) - Barclays Africa Group's <BGAJ.J> posted an expected 10 percent rise in first-half headline earnings on Wednesday boosted by its Africa operations.

The pan-African lender, majority owned by the eponymous British bank <BARC.L>, said headline earnings per share came in at 720.9 cents in the six months to end June, compared with a restated 655.7 cents a year ago.  Barclays said net interest income - the measure of income from lending - grew 10 percent to 17.197 billion rand ($1.62 billion) as the bank passed on higher interest rates.